# CRUCIBLE — OpenEnv Hackathon 2026

## Project
Multi-agent RL environment for procurement compliance (AXIOM Corp).
Stack: Python, FastAPI, OpenEnv v0.2.3, Groq API (dev) / HF Inference API (submission), Streamlit, Pydantic.
Agents: Executor, Arbiter, Architect, Vendor + RegulationShock engine.

## Hackathon submission non-negotiables
- Use OpenEnv base classes: Environment or MCPEnvironment only
- Respect client/server separation — clients never import server internals
- Implement exactly: reset(), step(), state() — never use these as MCP tool names
- Valid openenv.yaml manifest must exist
- Training script must connect to live HF Space environment, not a static dataset
- Push to HuggingFace Space via: openenv push --repo-id Flake56/crucible-env
- README must link: HF Space URL, training notebook, blog post, plots
- Plots committed as .png with axis labels — never left only in Colab or W&B

## Judging weights (keep these in mind on every decision)
- Environment Innovation: 40% — novel, adversarial, self-improving, multi-jurisdiction
- Storytelling: 30% — dashboard, README, counterfactual consequences
- Reward improvement: 20% — before/after curves, baseline comparison, +78% is your number
- Pipeline quality: 10% — composable reward, GRPO-ready, token-aware rate limiting

## LLM backend — TWO modes, never mix them up

### DEV mode (local, uses Groq free tier)
- Model: llama-3.1-8b-instant via groq SDK
- Hard limit: 500K tokens/day free tier (your logs show you hit this at 18:00 and 22:00)
- Real numbers from your logs: avg 1,209 input tokens, avg 381 output tokens, 58.2% success rate, 41.8% 429s
- Rate limit type: TPD (tokens per day) — NOT TPM. Parse retry-after from error with: re.search(r"try again in ([\d.]+)([sm])", err)

### SUBMISSION mode (HF Inference API, uses $30 HF credit per person)
- Model: meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct via HF Inference API
- Export: HF_TOKEN=hf_your_token
- Budget: ~$30 per person, T4 GPU for training via hf jobs uv run --flavor t4-small

## Groq rules (DEV mode only)
- System prompts are STATIC strings — never f-string or .format() a system prompt
- All dynamic content (scenario, task JSON, attempt) goes in the user turn only
- max_tokens per agent: Arbiter=450, Executor=600, Architect=400, Vendor=500
- Backoff: parse exact retry-after from 429 error message, wait that duration, max 5 retries
- Daily budget guard: module-level counter, raise BudgetExhausted if remaining < requested

## Code rules
- Pydantic models for all Action/Observation/State
- No FAR/DFARS clause text hardcoded in prompts — use CLAUSE_LOOKUP dict
- Episode logs ? data/episode_logs/ as JSON
- Plots ? plots/*.png with labeled axes, committed to repo
- Return JSON only from all LLM calls — enforce with "Return JSON only." in every system prompt
